ty.com/rules/axe/4.12/aria-meter-name"><span>Learn how to name <code>meter</code> elements</span></a>.</span><span class="lh-audit__adorn" title="This audit does not contribute to the overall category score.">Unscored</span></div> <div class="lh-audit__stackpacks"></div> </details> </div><div class="lh-audit lh-audit--notapplicable lh-audit--pass" id="aria-progressbar-name"> <details class="lh-expandable-details"> <summary> <div class="lh-audit__header lh-expandable-details__summary"> <span class="lh-audit__score-icon"></span> <span class="lh-audit__title-and-text"> <span class="lh-audit__title"><span>ARIA <code>progressbar</code> elements have accessible names</span></span> <span class="lh-audit__display-text"></span> </span> <div class="lh-chevron-container"><svg class="lh-chevron" viewBox="0 0 100 100"> <g class="lh-chevron__lines"> <path class="lh-chevron__line lh-chevron__line-left" d="M10 50h40"></path> <path class="lh-chevron__line lh-chevron__line-right" d="M90 50H50"></path> </g> </svg></div> </div> </summary> <div class="lh-audit__description"><span><span>When a <code>progressbar</code> element doesn't have an accessible name, screen readers announce it with a generic name, making it unusable for users who rely on screen readers. </span><a rel="noopener" target="_blank" href="https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/4.12/aria-progressbar-name"><span>Learn how to label <code>progressbar</code> elements</span></a>.</span><span class="lh-audit__adorn" title="This audit does not contribute to the overall category score.">Unscored</span></div> <div class="lh-audit__stackpacks"></div> </details> </div><div class="lh-audit lh-audit--notapplicable lh-audit--pass" id="aria-prohibited-attr"> <details class="lh-expandable-details"> <summary> <div class="lh-audit__header lh-expandable-details__summary"> <span class="lh-audit__score-icon"></span> <span class="lh-audit__title-and-text"> <span class="lh-audit__title"><span>Elements use only permitted ARIA attributes</span><